{% # Inline Asset v1.0.0 -%}

{%- doc %}
  @description
  Safe wrapper around `| inline_asset_content`. Returns nothing when input is blank or when the filter signals an error (missing asset / unsupported extension). Always prefer this over raw `inline_asset_content` — the raw filter crashes on blank input and emits a literal `<!-- inline_asset_content: ... -->` comment on error which is harmless in <style>, breaks ES modules in <script>, and renders empty in <svg>.

  Whitespace trim markers (`{%-` / `-%}`) are required on the structural tags so the snippet emits exactly the asset content (or nothing) — without them, captured output gains 5 newlines from the source layout, which leak into <style>/<svg> contexts.

  @param {string} asset_name - Asset filename to inline (e.g. `core.css`, `icon-chevron.svg`). Blank or error → empty output.

  @example {% capture css %}{% render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: 'core.css' %}{% endcapture %}
  @example {% capture icon_markup %}{% render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: 'icon-chevron.svg' %}{% endcapture %}
{%- enddoc %}

{%- liquid
  if asset_name == blank
    break
  endif
  assign result = asset_name | inline_asset_content
  if result contains '<!-- inline_asset_content:'
    break
  endif
  echo result
-%}
